cipeIngredient":["2 tablespoons light-tasting oil ((vegetable, mild olive, canola))","1  red bell pepper (, chopped)","1  small yellow onion (, chopped)","2 cloves garlic (, minced)","2 cups cooked black beans (, in 3\/4 cup reserved cooking liquid*)","1\/4 cup Salsa Lizano (**)","3 cups cooked rice (, preferably, day-old and refrigerated)","1\/4 cup chopped fresh cilantro"],"recipeInstructions":[{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat until shimmering. Sauté chopped bell pepper and onions until peppers are soft and onions are translucent, about 6-8 minutes. Add minced garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.","name":"Heat oil in a large skillet over medium-high heat until shimmering. Sauté chopped bell pepper and onions until peppers are soft and onions are translucent, about 6-8 minutes. Add minced garlic and cook for 1 minute, until fragrant.","url":"https:\/\/stripedspatula.com\/gallo-pinto\/#wprm-recipe-7474-step-0-0"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Add black beans, reserved cooking liquid, and Salsa Lizano, stirring to combine. Simmer for 5 minutes, until slightly thickened and little bit of the liquid is evaporated. Gently stir in cooked rice and cook until heated through and most of the liquid is absorbed, about 3-5 minutes.","name":"Add black beans, reserved cooking liquid, and Salsa Lizano, stirring to combine. Simmer for 5 minutes, until slightly thickened and little bit of the liquid is evaporated. Gently stir in cooked rice and cook until heated through and most of the liquid is absorbed, about 3-5 minutes.","url":"https:\/\/stripedspatula.com\/gallo-pinto\/#wprm-recipe-7474-step-0-1"},{"@type":"HowToStep","text":"Stir in chopped cilantro. Season to taste with additional Salsa Lizano, if desired, and serve.","name":"Stir in chopped cilantro. Season to taste with additional Salsa Lizano, if desired, and serve.","url":"https:\/\/stripedspatula.com\/gallo-pinto\/#wprm-recipe-7474-step-0-2"}],"aggregateRating":{"@type":"AggregateRating","ratingValue":"4.94","ratingCount":"63","reviewCount":"18"},"review":[{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"so yummy! I couldn't find Salsa Lizano anywhere  but Louisiana brand Smoked Chipotle sauce worked nicely. Next time I'll double the recipe because I easily eat half of it in one go.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Barbara Eberhart"},"datePublished":"2026-05-28"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Wife is half Costa Rican😎. This recipe makes me a superstar. Lozano is mandatory! Love it. In Costa Rica they add salt pork, I add a ham hock. So good","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Pat Morrill"},"datePublished":"2026-05-13"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I've made this recipe several times, and we love it! Thank you.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Eve"},"datePublished":"2026-05-03"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is by far the best gallo pinto recipe. My search has ended. So easy by cheating and using a can of organic black beans with the liquid. Needed only salt and pepper for my taste. Killer recipe, thank you.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Dawn"},"datePublished":"2026-04-26"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I love this recipe","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"elsie"},"datePublished":"2026-04-10"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is really delicious and easy to make.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Meredith Mednick"},"datePublished":"2026-01-12"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Beautiful recipe! I just got home from Costa Rica and I was craving their traditional gallo pinto and found this recipe. This hit the spot! So yummy and easy to make. Thank you for the recipe! Pura Vida!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Michelle Saunders"},"datePublished":"2026-01-06"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"My family has fallen in love with Costa Rica, and especially with the food there.  I tried a couple of  gallo pinto recipes after we returned but this one is the real deal.  My wife and daughter have now been spoiled - when we go back (or have rice and beans elsewhere) I inevitably hear \"Yeah, yours is still better.\"  I DO add a bit of MSG, overdo the garlic, and make it with a (probably inappropriate) basmati rice....but it's still Pura Vida for us :)","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Dave"},"datePublished":"2026-01-04"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"We have been to Costa Rica and we just tested this recipe.  It's the closest we can get to eating this dish in Costa Rica(Pura Vida).  Lizano sauce makes the difference.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Rich Ermolovich"},"datePublished":"2025-12-22"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Made this recipe for an “Around the World” elective when we studied Costa Rica. At the end of the class, when asked which dish was their favorite, this Gallo Pinto won by a landslide!\r\n\r\nNow I make it at home regularly, using your black bean recipe as well!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jillian Gosselin"},"datePublished":"2025-11-22"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"We’ve not been to Costa Rica, but found this recipe, ordered the sauce from Amazon and finally made the dish last weekend. We loved it!  My husband asked for it again this week!  I’d say it is a BIG hit. Making rice now so that it will be ready for preparation tomorrow!  Thanks for sharing!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Kerry Ray"},"datePublished":"2025-09-06"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Made with a Salsa Lizano substitute and then with the real thing after an Amazon order. No comparison so don’t make it unless you have the real thing. Haven’t been to CR since 2004 and was instantly taken back there - great recipe, thank you 🤩","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Tom"},"datePublished":"2025-08-11"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I made this and it is exactly what I’ve enjoyed on my trips to Costa Rica. The Lizano salsa is critical and available from Amazon. I had cooked a big pot of black beans and I was looking for what else I might use them in: Gallo Pinto came up. Having the bean liquid really made a difference. Thanks for sharing!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Debra McBride"},"datePublished":"2025-07-04"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"We went to Costa Rica on a 21 day vacation that covered most of the country. It was amazing, friendly, interesting and so beautiful. We fell in love with Gallo Ponto and thanks to this recipe we can relive our lazy morning brunch with this dish whisking us back there!!!\r\nThanks for posting this xx","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Tony"},"datePublished":"2025-06-19"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is it, folks.  With good black beans, this recipe finally captured what I feel\/felt about Gallo Pinto.  Don't let it stay too wet, DO add optional flavourings as required (I like cumin and bird's eye chilis).","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Dave"},"datePublished":"2025-05-13"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"I am cooking meals from all the countries in order. I use the online food community a lot in finding dishes to cook and sourcing ingredients. This is  a great example for Costa Rica. Recipe is clear and well explained. Thank you for the email option too.","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Jenny"},"datePublished":"2024-09-14"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"This is such an amazing recipe!! I made it last night and it took me right back to the first time I visited Costa Rica in 2016. Will be making this more often. Thank you!!","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"mary"},"datePublished":"2024-07-02"},{"@type":"Review","reviewRating":{"@type":"Rating","ratingValue":"5"},"reviewBody":"Me as a costarican i think its very good","author":{"@type":"Person","name":"Leo"},"datePublished":"2024-04-11"}],"recipeCategory":["Breakfast","Side Dish"],"recipeCuisine":["Costa Rican"],"nutrition":{"@type":"NutritionInformation","calories":"165 kcal","carbohydrateContent":"28 g","proteinContent":"5 g","fatContent":"4 g","sodiumContent":"352 mg","fiberContent":"4 g","sugarContent":"2 g","servingSize":"0.125 recipe","saturatedFatContent":"0.4 g","transFatContent":"0.01 g","unsaturatedFatContent":"3 g"},"@id":"https:\/\/stripedspatula.com\/gallo-pinto\/#recipe","isPartOf":{"@id":"https:\/\/stripedspatula.com\/gallo-pinto\/#article"},"mainEntityOfPage":"https:\/\/stripedspatula.com\/gallo-pinto\/"}]}</script>
